    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure to store essential, mutable SCB register values for backup/restore. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This structure only contains SCB registers that are safe and meaningful to backup and restore. In particular, registers that are read-only (such as CPUID) or contain volatile information (ICSR / CFSR) are ignored, since their value is tied to the system state or fixed in hardware, rather than related to a configuration option. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
